And in 2013 we were on the shortlist for the Building Awards 'BIM Initiative of the Year'.

All of our procedures for Health, Safety, Quality, and Environmental are approved by ISO regulations.


Throughout the history of Speller Metcalfe we've received numerous awards and recognitions for our on-going approach to achieving innovation and excellence within the construction field.


These accomplishments are made attainable via our collaborative way of working with our customers, professional consultants and the building supply chain.


While growth slowed in the previous year across the building sector, our turnover has reached about GBP85 million and we expect this to continue to grow.


Our Living division is a great example of our success, doubling its anticipated turnover since its foundation in 2011, now belongs on the approved building contractors checklist for fifteen assorted housing associations.


And even with industry depression within the construction industry, Speller Metcalfe effectively overcame the recession with no need for firm-wide redundancies.


Thanks to our financial management and tight cost-control, we continue to remain a success within the construction industry.


The origins and business philosophy of Speller Metcalfe is centred upon striving for and achieving the highest standards of excellence as a leading construction company - from client relationships through to skills, and construction to work welfare.

Speller Metcalfe approaches each construction project with a friendly, positive outlook - driven by our obligation to our workforce.

Despite the difficulties many construction companies' face, our fiscal success and reputation within the building business encourage our clientele to get confidence in our brand.

Our committed workforce continues to drive Speller Metcalfe's success, and their unrelenting commitment to delivering high quality jobs within budget and on time.

lenders.name: Brielle Schwartz
lenders.occupational_info:
Brielle Schwartz was raised on a gentleman’s farm in Indiana. She is a second generation horsewoman, and she had her first Saddlebred horse as a small child. Brielle started showing horses by the age of eight. The culmination of a successful Junior Exhibitor career was earning a World’s Grand Champion three-gaited country pleasure title with her beloved American Saddlebred Boardroom Ace in 1999. She and Ace were named people’s choice and earned numerous high point and industry awards. Most recently Brielle and her World’s Champion Friesian, Kieran of Carisbrooke completed a 2012 show season earning six first place finishes.  Truly a first-rate equestrian competitor, Brielle has been competing in Saddle Seat horseback riding for more than 25 years.
After graduating from Indiana University, Brielle completed her commercial lending certification from the Indiana Banking Association at Butler University. She holds multiple professional licenses and has worked as a private banker, wealth manager, and sales leader.
Brielle’s passion for philanthropy led her to participate in the Miss America program for many years. She has dedicated countless hours to the Miss America Organization, raising awareness, funds, and having both competed as well as served as a local director in Indiana. Brielle has also been involved in a number of philanthropic initiatives including Camp Soaring Eagle, PATH International (Professional Association of Therapeutic Horsemanship International), speaking for the National Consumer’s League, the Indiana Jump Start Coalition, and served as the Indiana director for Lifesmarts for 3 years.
